37622>>>    // Add code to customize your Zoom View based on how it was invoked.
37622>>>    // Use NavigateData to determine the context this view will be used in.
37622>>>    Procedure OnNavigateForward tWebNavigateData NavigateData Integer hoInvokingView Integer hoInvokingObject
37625>>>
37625>>>        // if this view is being used in multiple contexts, you may need a block of code
37625>>>        // like this to handle customizations. This would include hiding rows and buttons
37625>>>        // (WebSet pbRender) and changing the values of various captions.
37625>>>        Case Begin
37625>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromMain)
37627>>>                // If from main, this is a probably a main file Select to Zoom.
37627>>>                // This is the most typical way to navigate to a zoom.
37627>>>                Case Break
37628>>>                
37628>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromParent)
37631>>>                // If from parent, this is a constrained drill down.
37631>>>                // If needed, you could check NavigateData.iTable to determine the constraining parent.
