37937>>>
37937>>>        // if this view is being used in multiple contexts, you may need a block of code
37937>>>        // like this to handle customizations. This would include hiding rows and buttons
37937>>>        // (WebSet pbRender) and changing the values of various captions.
37937>>>        Case Begin
37937>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromMain)
37939>>>                // If from main, this is a probably a main file Select to Zoom.
37939>>>                // This is the most typical way to navigate to a zoom.
37939>>>                Case Break
37940>>>                
37940>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromParent)
37943>>>                // If from parent, this is a constrained drill down.
37943>>>                // If needed, you could check NavigateData.iTable to determine the constraining parent.
37943>>>                // This would be unusual - normally you drill down from a parent to a list (Select view).
37943>>>                Case Break
37944>>>                
37944>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromChild)
37947>>>                // If from child, this is a probably a parent Zoom from a Zoom. 
37947>>>                // This is unusual, but it might be used for adding a new child record.
37947>>>                Case Break
37948>>>                
37948>>>            Case Else // must be nfUndefined
37948>>>                // This may be the start of a query or this may be used for some kind of custom operation.
37948>>>                // You may want to check NavigateData.NamedValues.
37948>>>                  
37948>>>        Case End
37948>>>
37948>>>        // Action buttons can be changed dynamically during a Zoom's display lifetime.
37948>>>        // It's best to set these buttons in their own procedure so you can change later.
37948>>>        Send SetActionButtons
37949>>>
37949>>>    End_Procedure
37950>>>
37950>>>End_Object
