38254>>>    // Add code to customize your Zoom View based on how it was invoked.
38254>>>    // Use NavigateData to determine the context this view will be used in.
38254>>>    Procedure OnNavigateForward tWebNavigateData NavigateData Integer hoInvokingView Integer hoInvokingObject
38257>>>
38257>>>        // if this view is being used in multiple contexts, you may need a block of code
38257>>>        // like this to handle customizations. This would include hiding rows and buttons
38257>>>        // (WebSet pbRender) and changing the values of various captions.
38257>>>        Case Begin
38257>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromMain)
38259>>>                // If from main, this is a probably a main file Select to Zoom.
38259>>>                // This is the most typical way to navigate to a zoom.
38259>>>                Case Break
38260>>>                
38260>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromParent)
38263>>>                // If from parent, this is a constrained drill down.
38263>>>                // If needed, you could check NavigateData.iTable to determine the constraining parent.
38263>>>                // This would be unusual - normally you drill down from a parent to a list (Select view).
38263>>>                Case Break
38264>>>                
38264>>>            Case (NavigateData.eNavigateType = nfFromChild)
38267>>>                // If from child, this is a probably a parent Zoom from a Zoom. 
38267>>>                // This is unusual, but it might be used for adding a new child record.
38267>>>                Case Break
38268>>>                
38268>>>            Case Else // must be nfUndefined
38268>>>                // This may be the start of a query or this may be used for some kind of custom operation.
38268>>>                // You may want to check NavigateData.NamedValues.
38268>>>                  
38268>>>        Case End
38268>>>
38268>>>        // Action buttons can be changed dynamically during a Zoom's display lifetime.
38268>>>        // It's best to set these buttons in their own procedure so you can change later.
38268>>>        Send SetActionButtons
38269>>>
38269>>>    End_Procedure
38270>>>
38270>>>End_Object
